		<h3>Imporatant Update: School Closure Begins Monday, March 16 for students.<br>
</h3>
		
		
		
		
		
			<p class="summary">COVID-19 Updates! March 14, 2020.</p>
		
		
		
			<span class="text rteSpan"><div>To our UPA Families,<br>
</div>
<div>          <br>
</div>
<div>            Earlier today, I sent communication to all staff and families outlining our plan for next week in response
to COVID-19 (coronavirus). Our plan was based on current information that we had from state officials.
At 4:24pm today I received an email from the Office of Charter Schools indicating that the Governor and
State Superintendent ordered all public schools to close for at least two weeks—March 16th through
March 30th tentatively. The very best thing we can do to prevent the spread is to follow all guidelines of
our federal, state and local authorities.
Campus will be open Monday, March 16th as a teacher workday. Any student who needs to pick up
headphones, school supplies, books, or personal items will be able to do so during normal school hours.
It is necessary at this point to move to eLearning and we ask your cooperation in having your child
participate in the online/remote learning plan we have developed. Online learning will begin on March
18th
. I would like to emphasize that we understand that each family will have different needs and
challenges during this time, and we are working to make a plan that is flexible and supportive.
All communication and resources are available in one location: https://indiantrailprep.org/apps/staff/
We will put together a plan to sign out school devices for those students who need it. Teachers are
planning flexible learning activities for those who do not have access. All support teachers,
interventionists, as well as our AIG instructor are working on plans for tutoring and one on one
instruction. Mrs. Curry, our school counselor, will be continuing her work through phone and video
chat. Our instructional assistants will also be working with students.
I would like to stress that this is an unprecedented situation with significant impact to our community. I
will keep in touch with you via email, Facebook, Edmodo, text and phone as we progress. Thank you for
your continued support and patience.
<br>
</div>
<div><br></div>
<div>Sincerely,
Alison Simpson, Principal<br>
</div></span><br><div align="right">
		<br clear="both"><br>
</div>
		
		
		
	
		
		
		
		
		
